text.tspan: Prevalence of undernourishment vs share of children who are stunted, 2000
Childhood stunting is the share of children younger than 5 years that are stunted, which means they fall are two standard
deviations from the median height-for-age of the WHO 'Child Growth Standards'.
Source: UN Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO)
